      "title": "Flowers In The Attic 1987 202510",
      "description": "Flowers in the Attic is a 1987 American psychological horror film directed by Jeffrey Bloom and starring Louise Fletcher, Victoria Tennant, Kristy Swanson, and Jeb Stuart Adams. It  follows the story of four siblings—Chris, Cathy, and twins Cory and Carrie—who are forced to live with their abusive grandmother after their father's death. Confined to an attic and subjected to neglect and cruelty, they struggle to survive while uncovering dark family secrets, including the incestuous nature of their parents' relationship.",
